---
id: org.dxos.plugin.calls
name: CallsPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

WebRTC video / audio conferencing for `DXOS` Composer.

`plugin-calls` owns everything required to join, render, and leave a multi-party
real-time call. It carries no persistent schema of its own — calls are attached
to existing objects (typically `Channel`, but pluggable) via a `roomId` derived
from the object's DXN. Persistent meeting records, transcripts and summaries
live in `plugin-meeting`, which composes on top of this plugin's
`CallsCapabilities.Manager` and `EventHandler`.

This plugin is the result of extracting all video-call functionality out of
`plugin-thread`. After the split `plugin-thread` is concerned with chat,
threaded comments, and the `Channel` ECHO type only; `plugin-calls` is
concerned with the live call surface.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`        |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`        |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`        |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`   |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`          |
| `service`   | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`     |
| `capability`| `org.dxos.mdl.capability@1.0`  |

## Types

```mdl
type RoomId
  desc: |
    Stable identifier for a call room.
    Currently derived from the DXN of the host object (typically a Channel),
    but the surface treats it as opaque.
  fields:
    value: string
```

```mdl
type Participant
  desc: A peer in an active call, including self.
  fields:
    identityDid: string
    displayName?: string
    isSelf: boolean
    isSpeaking: boolean
    handRaised: boolean
    pinned: boolean
    tracks: TrackBundle
```

```mdl
type TrackBundle
  desc: The media tracks associated with one participant.
  fields:
    audio?: MediaStreamTrack
    video?: MediaStreamTrack
    screenshare?: MediaStreamTrack
```

```mdl
type MediaToggles
  desc: Local capture state. Each toggle reflects the *requested* state; the
        actual track may be muted or pending.
  fields:
    audio: boolean
    video: boolean
    screenshare: boolean
```

```mdl
type CallState
  desc: Aggregate view of the local participant's call session.
  fields:
    joined: boolean
    roomId?: RoomId
    self?: Participant
    users: Participant[]
    audioTracksToPlay: MediaStreamTrack[]
```

```mdl
type MediaState
  desc: Snapshot of the local media pipeline used for analytics and debugging.
  fields:
    audio: TrackInfo
    video: TrackInfo
    screenshare: TrackInfo
```

```mdl
type TrackInfo
  fields:
    enabled: boolean
    muted: boolean
    deviceId?: string
    trackId?: string
```

```mdl
type SessionId
  desc: Opaque identifier for a Cloudflare Calls SFU session.
  fields:
    value: string
```

```mdl
type TrackId
  desc: Identifier for a media track within the SFU.
  fields:
    value: string
```

```mdl
type LocalTrack
  desc: A media track produced by the local device and pushed to the SFU.
  fields:
    id: TrackId
    kind: "audio" | "video" | "screenshare"
    label: string
```

```mdl
type RemoteTrack
  desc: A media track received from a remote participant via the SFU.
  fields:
    id: TrackId
    kind: "audio" | "video" | "screenshare"
    participantId: string
```

```mdl
type SpeakingHandle
  desc: Opaque token returned by SpeakingMonitor.watch(); passed back to stop().
  fields: {}
```

## Capabilities

```mdl
capability CallsCapabilities.Manager
  desc: |
    Singleton service that owns the WebRTC session: joining a room, exposing
    self/users/track state as atoms, and toggling local media. Survives for
    the lifetime of the Client.
  type: CallManager
  events: [client-ready]

capability CallsCapabilities.EventHandler
  desc: |
    Pluggable per-call lifecycle callback. Contributors (e.g. plugin-meeting,
    plugin-transcription) react to join / leave / state changes without
    being coupled to the host object.
  type: CallProperties
  multi: true
```

## Components

```mdl
component CallArticle
  desc: The in-call surface — participant grid plus floating toolbar.
  props:
    roomId: RoomId
    fullscreen?: boolean
  state:
    self: Participant
    users: Participant[]
    audioTracksToPlay: MediaStreamTrack[]
  slots:
    toolbar?: ReactNode          # optional override; defaults to built-in Toolbar
  actions:
    leave()
    pin(participant: Participant)
    raiseHand()
    toggleAudio()
    toggleVideo()
    toggleScreenshare()
  emits:
    onLeave()
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────┐
    │ <hidden> audio mixer    │
    ├─────────────────────────┤
    │                         │
    │   participant grid      │
    │                         │
    │                         │
    ├─────────────────────────┤
    │     [Toolbar slot]      │
    └─────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component ParticipantGrid
  desc: Responsive grid of Participant tiles.
  props:
    self: Participant
    users: Participant[]
    debug?: boolean
    fullscreen?: boolean
  state:
    pinned?: Participant         # promoted to focus area
```

```mdl
component ParticipantTile
  desc: Single participant — video, name, mute/hand indicators.
  props:
    participant: Participant
    debug?: boolean
  emits:
    onPin()
```

```mdl
component Toolbar
  desc: Bottom-floating media controls.
  props:
    isInRoom: boolean
    channel?: Channel             # host object — drives "share link" affordance
  emits:
    onLeave()
  actions:
    toggleAudio()
    toggleVideo()
    toggleScreenshare()
    raiseHand()
    shareLink()
```

```mdl
component Lobby
  desc: Pre-join surface. Shown when display name is missing or when a
        preview is required before connecting.
  props:
    channel?: Channel
  state:
    displayName: string
  emits:
    onJoin()
```

```mdl
component CallDebugPanel
  desc: Devtools surface exposing CallState / MediaState / WebRTC stats.
  props:
    state: CallState
```

## Services

```mdl
service CallsService
  desc: |
    HTTP client for the Cloudflare Calls SFU. Provisions tracks for a session,
    pulls remote tracks, and tears them down on leave.
  ops:
    createSession() → SessionId
    pushTracks(session: SessionId, tracks: LocalTrack[]) → RemoteTrack[]
    pullTracks(session: SessionId, ids: TrackId[]) → MediaStreamTrack[]
    closeSession(session: SessionId)
  errors:
    SessionUnavailable: SFU rejected the session
  effects: [http]
```

```mdl
service CallSwarmSynchronizer
  desc: |
    Discovers peers in a room via DXOS swarm signalling and shares each
    peer's TrackBundle so remote tracks can be pulled from the SFU.
  ops:
    join(roomId: RoomId) → Participant[]
    leave(roomId: RoomId)
    publish(state: TrackBundle)
  events:
    onPeerJoin(peer: Participant)
    onPeerLeave(peer: Participant)
    onPeerStateChanged(peer: Participant)
  effects: [network]
```

```mdl
service MediaManager
  desc: Owns local media devices and produces the local TrackBundle.
  ops:
    requestAudio() → MediaStreamTrack
    requestVideo() → MediaStreamTrack
    requestScreenshare() → MediaStreamTrack
    stop(track: MediaStreamTrack)
  errors:
    PermissionDenied: user denied media access
    DeviceUnavailable: requested device not present
  effects: [device]
```

```mdl
service SpeakingMonitor
  desc: |
    Analyses audio tracks and emits an isSpeaking signal per participant.
    Consumed by `plugin-transcription` to gate transcripts on speech.
  ops:
    watch(track: MediaStreamTrack) → SpeakingHandle
    stop(handle: SpeakingHandle)
  effects: [audio-analysis]
```

## Operations

```mdl
op startCall
  desc: |
    Joins the call for `roomId`, invoking `EventHandler.onJoin` for every
    registered EventHandler after the local session is established.
  input:
    roomId: RoomId
    channel?: Channel             # passed through to extensions
  effects: [device, network]
  requires: [CallsCapabilities.Manager]
  errors:
    DisplayNameMissing: identity has no display name set
    PermissionDenied: media permission denied
    SessionUnavailable: SFU unreachable
```

```mdl
op leaveCall
  desc: |
    Tears down the local session, turns off audio/video/screenshare,
    and invokes `EventHandler.onLeave` for every registered EventHandler.
  input:
    roomId?: RoomId
  effects: [device, network]
  requires: [CallsCapabilities.Manager]
```

```mdl
op toggleAudio
  input:
    enabled: boolean
  requires: [CallsCapabilities.Manager]
  effects: [device]
```

```mdl
op toggleVideo
  input:
    enabled: boolean
  requires: [CallsCapabilities.Manager]
  effects: [device]
```

```mdl
op toggleScreenshare
  input:
    enabled: boolean
  requires: [CallsCapabilities.Manager]
  effects: [device]
```

```mdl
op raiseHand
  input:
    raised: boolean
  requires: [CallsCapabilities.Manager]
```

```mdl
op pinParticipant
  input:
    identityDid: string
    pinned: boolean
  requires: [CallsCapabilities.Manager]
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Start Call from a Channel

  req F-1.1: Channel article surface shows a "Start video call" action
             in its toolbar (contributed via a graph type-extension on
             Channel). plugin-thread itself does not know about calls.

  req F-1.2:
    when: user invokes the Start video call action and has a display name
    then: op:startCall(roomId: DXN(channel)) is invoked; CallArticle becomes
          visible as a deck companion ("Active Call") alongside the chat
    errors: [PermissionDenied, SessionUnavailable]

  req F-1.3:
    when: user invokes the Start video call action and has no display name
    then: Lobby is shown; on save of display name, op:startCall is invoked
    errors: [DisplayNameMissing]
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Active Call Companion

  req F-2.1:
    when: CallState.joined === true
    then: an "Active Call" deck companion is contributed by the AppGraph
          builder; selecting it surfaces the CallArticle
          (Surface id: `deck-companion--active-call`)

  req F-2.2:
    when: CallState.joined === true and roomId matches the focused Channel
    then: a "Chat" companion appears on the Channel so the user can switch
          back to the chat plank
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Participant Grid

  req F-3.1: ParticipantGrid lays out self + remote users responsively, up
             to fullscreen.
  req F-3.2: ParticipantTile shows mute, hand-raised, and speaking
             indicators sourced from CallState / SpeakingMonitor.
  req F-3.3:
    when: user clicks Pin on a tile
    then: that participant is promoted to the focus region; state is local
          to the current peer only
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Media Controls

  req F-4.1: Toolbar exposes toggles for microphone, camera, screenshare,
             raise-hand, and a Leave button.
  req F-4.2:
    when: user toggles a media control
    then: corresponding op:toggleX runs; MediaManager updates the local
          track; track changes propagate to peers via CallSwarmSynchronizer

  req F-4.3:
    when: user clicks Leave
    then: op:leaveCall runs; audio / video / screenshare tracks are stopped;
          CallArticle and the "Active Call" companion disappear
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Extension Lifecycle

  req F-5.1: Plugins may register CallsCapabilities.EventHandler with optional
             onJoin / onLeave / onCallStateUpdated / onMediaStateUpdated
             callbacks.
  req F-5.2:
    when: op:startCall completes
    then: every registered EventHandler.onJoin is invoked once with
          { channel, roomId }

  req F-5.3:
    when: CallState changes
    then: every registered EventHandler.onCallStateUpdated is invoked with the
          new state

  req F-5.4:
    when: local MediaState changes (e.g. mic toggled, speech detected)
    then: every registered EventHandler.onMediaStateUpdated is invoked with
          [mediaState, isSpeaking]

  req F-5.5:
    when: op:leaveCall runs
    then: every registered EventHandler.onLeave is invoked with the prior roomId
```

```mdl
feat F-6: Lobby / Display Name Gate

  req F-6.1: Users without a profile.displayName cannot join a call.
  req F-6.2:
    when: a user without a display name attempts to join
    then: Lobby is rendered (CallArticle is replaced by Lobby) with a
          display-name form
  req F-6.3:
    when: user submits a display name in the Lobby
    then: identity.updateProfile({ displayName }) is invoked; op:startCall
          resumes automatically
```

```mdl
feat F-7: Devtools Surface

  req F-7.1: A `devtools-overview` surface is contributed showing CallState
             (joined, users, audio tracks) and the most recent MediaState.
  req F-7.2: WebRTC stats from `@peermetrics/webrtc-stats` are surfaced for
             diagnostic use.
```

```mdl
feat F-8: Independence from plugin-thread

  req F-8.1: plugin-calls MUST NOT depend on plugin-thread at runtime.
             It depends only on `@dxos/types` for the Channel type.

  req F-8.2: plugin-thread MUST NOT depend on plugin-calls at runtime.
             plugin-thread's Channel article renders chat only; the
             "Start video call" action is contributed externally via a
             graph type-extension.

  req F-8.3:
    when: plugin-calls is not registered
    then: plugin-thread renders Channel articles as chat-only without
          error; no missing-capability warnings appear

  req F-8.4: Existing consumers of `ThreadCapabilities.CallManager` /
             `CallExtension` migrate to `CallsCapabilities.Manager` /
             `CallsCapabilities.EventHandler`. The thread capability names
             are removed.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Join a call from a Channel
  given: a Channel article is open and the identity has a display name
  when: user clicks "Start video call"
  then:
    - op:startCall runs with roomId = DXN(channel)
    - CallState.joined === true
    - CallState.roomId === DXN(channel)
    - "Active Call" deck companion appears
    - local audio + video tracks are published to the SFU
```

```mdl
test T-2: Concurrent chat + call
  given: in a call on Channel X
  when: user navigates back to the Channel X article
  then:
    - Channel article continues to render ChannelChat (not the grid)
    - "Active Call" companion is still mounted with CallArticle
    - both surfaces are scrollable independently
```

```mdl
test T-3: Leave a call
  given: CallState.joined === true on roomId R
  when: user clicks Leave
  then:
    - op:leaveCall runs
    - MediaManager.stop is called for audio / video / screenshare
    - CallState.joined === false
    - "Active Call" companion disappears
    - every registered EventHandler.onLeave(R) is invoked
```

```mdl
test T-4: Display-name gate
  given: identity.profile.displayName is undefined
  when: user clicks "Start video call"
  then:
    - Lobby is shown
    - op:startCall is NOT invoked
    - on submitting a display name, identity.updateProfile runs and
      op:startCall is invoked automatically
```

```mdl
test T-5: Extension receives lifecycle callbacks
  given: a contributor has registered CallsCapabilities.EventHandler with
         onJoin / onLeave callbacks
  when: a call is started then ended
  then:
    - onJoin called exactly once with { channel, roomId }
    - onLeave called exactly once with roomId
```

```mdl
test T-6: plugin-thread renders without plugin-calls
  given: composer-app registers ThreadPlugin but NOT CallsPlugin
  when: a Channel article is opened
  then:
    - ChannelChat renders normally
    - no "Start video call" action is visible
    - no missing-capability errors are logged
```

```mdl
test T-7: Media toggle
  given: in a call, microphone is on
  when: user clicks the mic-off button in the Toolbar
  then:
    - op:toggleAudio({ enabled: false }) runs
    - local audio track is muted within 100ms
    - remote peers observe the muted track via swarm-synchronised state
```

```mdl
test T-8: SpeakingMonitor signal
  given: SpeakingMonitor is watching the local audio track
  when: the user speaks above the threshold for 300ms
  then:
    - CallState.self.isSpeaking === true
    - EventHandler.onMediaStateUpdated is invoked with isSpeaking === true
```

```mdl
test T-9: Devtools surface displays call diagnostics
  given: CallState.joined === true and the devtools panel is open
  when: user views the CallDebugPanel in the devtools-overview surface
  then:
    - CallState is displayed (joined, users, audio tracks)
    - MediaState is displayed (audio, video, screenshare info)
    - WebRTC stats from @peermetrics/webrtc-stats are visible
```

